article.description: Macie Michelson had eight points and Maria Boever added seven points as South Dakota State defeated Western Illinois 52-31 on Saturday for an eighth-straight win.
article.headline: Michelson, Boever lead South Dakota State to 8th straight win
article.linkText: South Dakota State cruises to 8th win in a row
article.story:
MACOMB, Ill. -- Macie Michelson had eight points and Maria Boever added seven points as South Dakota State (No. 20 ESPN/USA Today, No. 24 AP)
 defeated Western Illinois 52-31 on Saturday for an eighth-straight win.

South Dakota State (22-2, 11-1 Summit League) led by five points going into half time with a 25-20 score. Western Illinois (7-16, 5-7 Summit League) managed just 11 points in the second period.

Jantine Kraak led Western Illinois with 10 points, while Jennifer Warkenthien had a game-high eight rebounds for South Dakota State. The Jackrabbits had 42 rebounds and 14 assists.
